definition: to move out (vacate)/to shift sth out
to move (i.e. relocate oneself)/to move (sth relatively heavy or bulky)/to shift/to copy indiscriminately

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)

to go/to go to (a place)/(of a time etc) last/just passed/to send/to remove/to get rid of/to reduce/to be apart from in space or time/to die (euphemism)/to play (a part)/(when used either before or after a verb) to go in order to do sth/(after a verb of motion indicates movement away from the speaker)/(used after certain verbs to indicate detachment or separation)

sentences.english: Well, I'm gonna move out anyway.
sentences.chinese: 额，无论怎样，我都要搬出去。

sentences.english: Some day I vill paint a masterpiece, and ve shall all go away.
sentences.chinese: 总有一天我要画一幅杰作，我们就可以都搬出去了。

sentences.english: He told me I had to start paying rent, or move out.
sentences.chinese: 他说我得开始付房租，要么就搬出去。

sentences.english: The present householder will move out by this weekend and I'll move in by next Wednesday.
sentences.chinese: 目前的住户本周未搬出去，我下星期三搬进去。

sentences.english: At present, the householder doesn't move out, so I am about to move in next Wednesday.
sentences.chinese: 目前的住户本周未搬出去，我下星期三搬进去。

sentences.english: I’m still hoping, planning, to move out.
sentences.chinese: 但我仍希望着有一天我可以搬出去。

sentences.english: When I reached my senior year, I decided to move away for college.
sentences.chinese: 升读高三时，我决定读大学后从家里搬出去。

sentences.english: A: So, are you going to move out?
Kim asks her mother why Jack had moved out.
sentences.chinese: 金姆问她母亲，为何杰克搬出去住过。

sentences.english: Otherwise, he might as well move out of the White House, and hand the keys over to the Tea Party.
sentences.chinese: 不然，他还不如从白宫搬出去，将大权交给茶会党。

sentences.english: So, are you going to move out?
The present owner will move out this weekend ,so I will move in next wednesday .
sentences.chinese: 目前的住户本周未搬出去，我下星期三搬进去。

sentences.english: She had a fight with her family and moved out.
sentences.chinese: 她跟家人大吵一架就搬出去住。

sentences.english: Then everything just started up again. Normaden was moved out, and Andy was living in solitary splendour again.
sentences.chinese: 诺曼登搬出去后，安迪又再度享受到独居的优惠。

sentences.english: The couple moved out and Mr. Tan moved in. Mr.
sentences.chinese: 那对男女搬出去之后又住进来一位潭先生。

sentences.english: He is going to move out, do not always say uncle sister-in-law, the family man.
sentences.chinese: 他要搬出去住，大嫂不依，说二叔永远是这个家的人。
